			<title>[ June 3, 2024 -  June 7, 2024] Conference or similar: Heidegger on the Essence of Truth</title>
			<link>https://philevents.org/event/show/118153</link>
						<description>Venue: Boston University<br/><br/><p>The seminar will critically examine Heidegger’s transformative re-thinking of essence and truth in his 1930 essay “On the Essence of Truth,” marking a self-described “new beginning” in his philosophy. Participants, restricted to recent PHDs (since 2018) and advanced doctoral students must apply with CV and letter of intent. Up to six individuals will be accepted for the intense week of summer classes from June 3 to 7 on the Boston University campus.Travel, housing and food for the duration of the classes will be paid by <em>JHP </em>up to $2,000.  Go to https://jhp.wisc.edu/summerseminar.html for more details.</p></description>
